# TUI Architecture — Bubble Tea Wizard

## State Machine
- All wizard states live in `AppState` enum in `internal/tui/app.go`
- New states must be added to: the enum, `handleKeyPress`, `View()`, `updateViewSizes`, `getCurrentHelpItems`
- State transitions go through dedicated `transitionTo*` methods

## Views
- Each screen is a separate struct in `internal/tui/views/`
- Every view must implement: `SetSize(w, h int)`, `Render() string`, `GetHelpItems() []HelpItem`
- Views receive data via constructor or setter — never access App state directly

## Services
- Business logic lives in `internal/services/` (growth engine, auth, config)
- Services communicate with the TUI via `tea.Msg` types defined in `app.go`
- Async operations return `tea.Cmd` functions

## Components
- Reusable UI widgets live in `internal/tui/components/`
- Components are stateless renderers where possible

## Styling
- All colors and styles use `internal/tui/styles/` — never hardcode colors
- Use `lipgloss` for layout, `termenv` for adaptive theming
